6 The commission may issue a license to an out-of-state applicant, who holds a
7 cosmetology-related license that is not equivalent to a cosmetology, nail technology, or
8 esthetics license in this state, if the applicant possesses sufficient work experience to
9 qualify for enough work experience credit to compensate for any deficiency in education
10 hours, as set forth in rules of the commission, and otherwise meets the requirements of
11 this section. The work experience must be relevant to the license sought by the applicant.
12 Section 3. No later than September 1, 2026, the Cosmetology Commission shall, pursuant
13 to chapter 1-26, provide for and file with the secretary of state, the amendment of
14 § 20:42:03:06.01, as set forth below:
15 20:42:03:06.01. Applicant for licensure by reciprocity allowed credit for
16 work experience. An applicant for licensure by reciprocity may be allowed credit for work
17 experience as follows:
18 (1) Cosmetologist license:, a maximum of 750 seven hundred fifty hours of the
19 school education hours required in § 20:42:06:09 may be earned through work
20 experience. Two hours of work experience equals one hour of school education. If the
21 applicant obtained the work experience more than five years before the date of the
22 application, the applicant must take a commission-approved safety and infection control
23 procedures course in order to receive credit for the work experience;
24 (2) Nail technician license:, a maximum of 200 two hundred hours of the school
25 education hours required in § 20:42:06:09.01 may be earned through work experience.
26 Two hours of work experience equals one hour of school education. If the applicant
27 obtained the work experience more than five years before the date of the application, the
28 applicant must take a commission-approved safety and infection control procedures
29 course in order to receive credit for the work experience; and
30 (3) Esthetician license:, a maximum of 300 three hundred hours of the school
31 education hours required in § 20:42:06:09.02 may be earned through work experience.
32 Two hours of work experience equals one hour of school education. If the applicant
33 obtained the work experience more than five years before the date of the application, the
