14 Section 3. That a NEW SECTION be added to chapter 36-15:
15 If an applicant licensed by another state, district, territory, or foreign country holds a
16 cosmetology-related license that is not equivalent to a cosmetology, nail technology, or
17 esthetics license in this state, the commission must allow credit for relevant work experience
18 to apply toward the hours of education required for the cosmetology, nail technician, or
19 esthetics license, as applicable.
20 The commission shall credit two hours of work experience in the applicable field as one hour
21 of school education. Only work experience that occurred after the applicant was initially
22 licensed may be credited. The work experience hours may not be credited for more than half
23 of the hours of education required for the license.
24 The applicant shall submit documentation to the commission, in the form and manner required
25 by the commission, demonstrating the relevant work experience. The commission may deny
26 the issuance of a license, regardless of the amount of work experience submitted by the
27 applicant, if the commission determines that the applicant is not competent for the applicable
28 license.
29 If the applicant obtained the work experience more than five years before the date of
30 application, the commission may require the applicant to take a commission-approved safety
31 and infection control procedures course.
